identifications.body:
This is B. chloromelas, not B. pulcher. It's too far south for B. pulcher, and seems to have 25 scale rows (B. pulcher normally has 21).

And it's an iNat first - congratulations @thibaudaronson!

This is B. chloromelas, not B. pulcher. It's too far south for B. pulcher, and seems to have 25 scale rows (B. pulcher normally has 21).

And it's an iNat first - congratulations @thibaudaronson!
